ts were added after I got a bit deeper into it. So this game is mainly multi player, but has a single story mode. That one I was refering to in my first version of the review.Multiplayer is way more fun. BUT I have never seen more than 10 ppl online at the same time.In multiplayer there is a wide gap as to what you can do as rookie player compared to the pros, so expect to die a lot (and spend the rest of the mission watching) when you do not have a maxed out setup. And that takes sooooome time: There are 8 classes to be played, each has a specific level of 0 to 10 while you as the player have another level of 0 to 25 (that rises with any class). Some clases only become available after you have a certain amount of XP earned with others. This concept is quite cool as personal and class-individual bonuses stack. So once you have risen to a certain personal level (you advance both level types during play), this makes switching to a new class not as frustrating as starting at square one.So, you may have guessed it. This is obviously for ppl that have time to spare and really wanna get into it. Then again I think it's not that captivating (the story is always pretty much the same), but that is up to you. The mission items and objectives are not as dull as in some other games, but, well, after some time... they are pretty much the same.The same in all games to be honest. Yeah, you may switch the map, but the story unfolds all the same.The last paragraph containes the word ""same"" at least four times. That pretty much summs it up.To me this looks more like a decent beta version than a real game.I'll kook into this after some time.I am not convinced.And apart from saying so, it just has nothing to do with mars. It's just for the story.Tested version was 1.175"
