,Recommended,265590,30186744,Posted: 25 February,all,kschang77,"The Red Solstice starts as a pretty typical ""lone squad must defeat hordes of horrific creatures overrunning the colony"" plot, but manages to throw in several twists both in the game and in the plot to make things interesting. While the game can be played as a regular RTS, where you guide the squad and let them shoot anything in sight, by mission 4 or 5 you get curveballs, such as enemies that doesn't appear on sensors (so auto-aim doesn't work) but manual aimming does. Then you get into HUGE enemies (7500 hp!) that basically forces you to utilize each soldier's specialty power, such as gunship strafing, artillery beacon, grenade launcher, HE shells, so you can survive the fight. Gunship strafings can take out a large group of enemies, while artillery beacon can be placed then enemy lead over it so the barrage clean them out. Explosives can be placed, mines can be set, and so on. On the other hand, your soldiers can be seriously hit including poison, broken bones, septic wound, and more. Each soldier can only carry 6 items (some of which can have QTY > 1) so item management can be important as no one can carry everything. In RTS mode, movement controls are limited, but once you enter tactical mode, you can move soldiers about and give more individualized orders. Time also slows down tremendously, giving you time to give precise orders, like go here and kill that (and stay there).My main gripe with the game is difficulty in accessing all four members of the team, as usually you can only access the team leader. Only in tactical mode can you access all four members. This makes for a very awkward interface when you're the kind of guy that goes after every locker, where you could find inventory from bandages to explosvies.  These are the ""crates"" in this universe. But the increased reaction time makes entire mess actually doable. All in all, the tactical mode needs a bit polishing, otherwise it's one fun game."
,Recommended,265590,17020907,"Posted: 12 July, 2015",all,Azurose,"If you ever played the custom Warcraft 3 maps Night of the Dead or Dragoon, this game are those maps. Just as much replayability if not more than those maps and better graphics for sure! :D"
