76561198015968558,Recommended,265590,11291355,"Posted: 17 July, 2014",all,Takeda,"Ok so .. The Red Solstice .. apart from the really not great lobby and the 'we shall disconnect and crash the game - also for fun please redo the tutorial level before you're allowed to play multiplayer' problem, this is hard to fault.Think of space marines in any the following flavours: Warhammer/AVP/StarCraft and you'll be close to the kind of trooper feel the game has. You play one character and gain XP in 3 areas. The first is your XP (your account XP maybe) which gives you greater access to classes, weapons and perks as you progress. The second is your class XP - thus if you play medic alot you will unlock class specific 'powers'. The third is in-game XP - you start at the same basic level each new match and level within that match in a fashion similar to Dota or LoL etc. At the end of the match you lose that progression, but hey it's all good.Within the match there are items to be found. You only have 6 inventory slots so choose well and ammo is in short supply so it pays to grab it when you can and share with your team.Visually the game owes a lot to the Diablo 2 / Titans Quest / Warhammer view and it does look great, plus there is a lot of screen you cannot see due to poor lighting. Within buildings there are consoles which activate lights and flares which can be fired or dropped to help further. Also there are ad hoc sentry gun positions you can activate and within bunker mode, the option to deploy 'reinforcement' sentry turrets periodically.think i have done all i can to describe this game - noe go watch a youtube video on it"
