,Recommended,265590,17062743,"Posted: 15 July, 2015",all,oldSerge,"This is a great game, but not for everyone. I have only played the MP mode, and the game shows a lot of replayability, intensity, and teamwork moments. In MP, you control a single marine (usually) as you complete random missions with teammates.The point of the game is to complete as many missions and objectives as possible and then call for EVAC - before getting overrun. There can be up to 8 players in a single game, and each player can select the type of suit (class) and equipment they are taking on the mission. Classes range from Marksman, which is a sniper type of role, to Medics, Demolitions, Flamethrower, etc. The classes are varied, and have different upgrades which allows them to fulfill different roles.And that is what the game is all about - cooperation! As time goes on the enemy gets stronger and more numerous, supplies will run low, and people will start to die. Every moment becomes a tactical decision, and the smallest misstep can spell doom.  The enemy AI is not particularly clever, which is important because funnelling enemies into explosive death traps becomes very important, specially when you are facing one of the game's bosses.Death is painful, because there is no respawns - except for new players. If you are not a new player (determined by some threshold of character XP), then you stay dead until a medic can revive you or a special mission (""Reinforcements"") is completed by the team. (This mission becomes available about halfway through the game, and its availability by no means guarantees that you will be able to complete it!)The graphics and sounds are mediocre at best, functional at least. The music is slightly better. They will not turn you away from the game, but the game wont win any awards for any of these.Playing with friends is where its at - the game has a lot to explore, and that means a lot of death and discovery as you come to grips with the game. The game does have built in voice, and there is also a public TeamSpeak server which sees a lot of action. The community is friendly overall, and it is tight knight as is common with communities that form around hidden gems like this game.There seems to be a good amount of replayability - first because the game is HARD, second because of how missions are randomized. There are I think 6 maps total, but everyone is still playing the first (and easiest!) of these. I actually thought at first that there was only one map and that it was randomly generated. And this is because the maps are very large, and there is so much going on, that it took a few days before I realized map is not random.I got the game 48 hours ago and have not been able to stop playing it. It is a real nail-biting experience, the cooperative aspects works really well, and the community is there to support it and help it grow.All we need is you now!"
