76561197969533352,Recommended,265590,17083870,"Posted: 16 July, 2015",all,Laughing Man,"Very fun game alot of replayability for the price.  The game has a top down perspective with a rotatable camera, and is played via hot keys and issuing move and shoot commands via the mouse.  It plays akin to some custom games from war 3, and is reminiscent in how it feels playing to some of the old action games of the past like gauntlet and the like.  This game is hyper focused on team work, while certain classes and loadouts can get by soloing for a bit, everyone ends up having to group for surival.  Managing your ammo, explosives, CDs, and working as a team are the keys to this game.  Failing at any of those means death.Game truly shines in multiplayer but the singleplayer isn't bad and helps you get used to the game via its tactical mode that lets your slow everything down.  Multiplayer of course doesn't use that though.There are of course some negatives, the voice acting work in this game is really really bad, thankfully there isn't much of it.  There are also some poor ability descriptions leading to easy misunderstanding of how some things function.  There are also a few bugs (currently) that while not game breaking can be a slight annoyance.Still though I would reccomend picking this game up, its not an expensive game, and its certainly worth the cost for the hours you will get out of it."
76561197994300103,Recommended,265590,17084258,"Posted: 16 July, 2015",all,Phantombane,"The Red Solstice is a top down, strategy shooter that plays like a blend of quality custom Starcraft 2 maps and Alien Swarm. It pits you and up to 7 other Human controlled marines against hordes of the monstrosities created by the STROL virus. To survive and complete your objective you must work with your teamates,scavenging materials, making plans for the hectic closing moments of a match, and dispatching the various dangers you will encounter during your stay at Tharsis colony. A Typical match of The Red Solstice can last around an hour, so do not expect the typical drop in drop out style multiplayer that many games today utilize. keep this in mind when you put aside time to play the game.I would like to mention that this game is hard, and can be incredibly brutal at times. Excpect to die quite often as a new player, so don't feel put off by it, it happens to everyone. Despite the difficulty, failure still nets class and account experience for you rendering even a loss into meaningful progress of both in game XP as well as real life player skill. To help alleviate the difficulty for newcomers, a certain ammount of free automatic respawns are granted to players below a certain rank. Additionally, players seeking assistance can ask both the developers and the community for advice as this game has some of the most active devs and most helpful community members of any game I have ever played. The community has also prepared a variety of guides that cover almost every aspect of the game with an incredible ammount of detail, I highly recommend new players look over these.In conclusion, The Red Solstice is a very unique, and very fun game. It offers a large ammount of replayabillity in the multiplayer modes and a good ammount of content aimed at those who prefer single player activities. I wholeheartedly recommend this game to anyone willing to give it the modicum of patience required to learn its particular nuances."
