76561198118848547,Recommended,265590,19573557,"Posted: 8 December, 2015",all,Mc Fishy,"Since there are plenty reviews explain game's mechanic, I'll try to keep this short. Overall, TRS is a solid top down tactical survial shooting game.Due to the ""tactical"" element and a steep learning curve, the best gaming experience you get from this game is the fruition of the ability to cooperate, adapt, follow and understand the ""order"" of the team leader (experienced vet).TRS is quiet unforgiving for rookies, so the willingness to learn and stick with the game is a necessity. In order to prevent the unfair random-kicking in multiplayer mode and the risk of losing game due to the lack of knowledge on game's mechanic, I wholeheartedly recommend everyone (intent to play---casually playing----intent to be a pro):-Try the single player mode (for the tutorial mainly). It has a pretty good storyline.-Read those ""Everything"" guides by Bonzai101, Valore and Grizzly. (You're gonna be surprised by the amount of knowledge you may learn/miss out). Check out those in-depths about classes and game mechanics (leadership).-Get TeamSpeak (an app similar to RaidCall). ""Why"", you asked? Well, the best way to learn a game is by playing it. And it's good to have somebody with experience to explain/help through the preparation and ingame if you decide to skip reading the guides. Mic is not required, vet only need you to listen and understand.The code to the TRS community server is:ts.com-game.de+ Inevitably, there are good and bad players. Some will assist you, some just downright ignore or troll you to oblivion; but the majority of the player base will help you with welcome arms.-One last thing, invite your friend or introduce it to somebody closed to you. The biggest problem with TRS right now is lack of player. The community is too small at the moment.Well, That's all I have to say. I mostly play as Heavy Support, never get around to learn being a leader, cuz i enjoy being a slow♥♥♥♥♥supportive follower using a minigun to slow♥♥♥♥♥♥down and let people do the rest. And I'm still pretty ""new""to the game, despite 100+ hrs clock-in."
