76561197990980295,Recommended,265590,17255129,"Posted: 27 July, 2015",all,Faffy,"Red Solstice is a game that encourages grinding and memorization of map objectives (and it does this even over teamwork) in order to succeed.Typical games result in 1k - 2k experience for your selected class, and it takes about 10-20k experience to gain one rank in the suit (1% speed, critical rating, that sort of thing). Considering the number of classes there are and there are like 10 ranks in each suit, that is a lot of grinding.Victory leads to 5k - 6k experience but if you're a new player that will come to you few and far between. And being that each game typically consumes 40 minutes or more, it will still take a considerable amount of time to max out the suit of your preference.Red Solstice CAN be fun, but the combat tends to be a little bit less entertaining than I was hoping for. I play with auto-targeting for the most part and that actually takes a lot of the fun out of the genre, but necessary, because manual targeting isn't effective enough to take out the swarming armies the AI decides to throw at you.Game has a tiny community, average at best. Multiiplayer games can take some time to fill (for a newish game).Art can be hit or miss (portraits). No major complaints, but there isn't enough emphasis on the ""cool"" element of manning state-of-the-art space marine body armor running around gunning or torching down alien zombies. I don't ""feel"" it. Far fetched hope that this will be fixed."
