,Not Recommended,265590,11234967,"Posted: 14 July, 2014",all,Deadjack,"For the moment i can't recommand this game for everybody.Because...Instead of my last review [watch at the end of this one], i've won a game !This is amazing how good it is. Especially if you loose around 20 times before it ^^In fact the mission was different and, in my humble point of view, much better !All the team was droped from a space ship near a beacon.It must be protected until the end of a certain amount of enemy's waves.The beacon drops some supplies to help you in the battle, like sentry turrets, ammo and sand bags.All the difficulty was to build the defenses, set up traps, protect sentries and for me, keep the other guys alive until the end of days that came on us.And we made it !I was a Medic as usual. After so much failures, i could start to upgrade my character.The upgrade system is really cool, for each class you have a rank and defines how long you played this class, so the higher the better...Skills wich increase with levels: at the beginning too few, but with few levels... oh my ! That's so good to place a resurecting beacon during a hellish mission ! You can even call orbital drops to give stuff to your comrades or activate buffs to the whole team.You have new weapons in two different types: primary and secondary. The primary weapons really changes your way to engage, as a Medic i can choose at high rank a sniper rifle, the basic weapon is a weak assault rifle. The secondary give you some shotguns and explosivs weapons like a rotary grenade launcher,ect..Weapons are different between each classe. Medic: assault rifles. Demolisher: explosivs. Recon: smg. Heavy: minigun, ect...Your armor can be upgraded with 4 slots to receive some ""perks"". A bit complicate to use because each perks increase a statistic of the character but reduce an other one. You want to run faster ?allright but you will have less damages done... quite nasty :'(All of that is not too much to prepare yourself for the fire of the action.And this is really tought !As i said before you gonna die a lot. But winning is very rewarding. Like some few rares games like Arma or Dark Soul.Enemies are quite numerous and very violent. Every creature has stats (you can see them when you hover your mouse on them). The special events happens quite often, and a good planning is really rewarding, like using explosivs to make chain reactions and take down a boss or a huge horde of creature in one blow. But when your team is splitting... in general you won't stand a chance.Every classes needs skills to be mastered.As a Medic i needed quite some time to understand how to get exp correctly (missions or the most common slaving monsters to get xp). Xp give you the opportunity to increase the level of the skills you have choosen (you can only have 4).  The skill level is lost between each mission.And like many games, maps needs time to be understood because hunker in a building and defending is really difficult. Especially with the light system that influence the line of sight of the team and the accuracy for shooting enemies.So...This game is really good but really hard too with unfriendly players that doesn't give a sh... of what you say in game.It's a bit messy for now but with few updates... this is gonna be a gem !The Red Solstice is nice and needs to be played with friends.Alone you gonna hate it.So i recommand it for experienced player used to games really hardcore and ready to play with trusted fellow... for the others, wait a bit ^^.[Previous review: game not recommended]I was really disappointed. In the action you're just lost. You spend tons of time to search for gear in lockers. You always lack of something especially ammo. Shooting enemies is a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥especially due to the fact that firing in automatic mode is useless (automatic mode= your monkey see smtg he shoots. The problem, after 3 meters you miss all the time).The objectives are ♥♥♥♥ed up. In fact you spend so much time in gearing that you can't see what you have to do.There is no order in objectives or obvious triggers. You will have an AI which talks all the time and disturbs you by the same occasion.In general in the game is like that (when you are a medic like me):-Clicking all the time on the screen to move sucks...-Shotgun ammo allready depleeed ?-Where is that dude? His health is dropping too fast, stop running away from the team damm it !-Why are we scavenging? There is a mission to do!-This auto aim sucks.-Please AI, shut your damm mouth!-Oh no! I've spent points in the wrong skill section...-This player is a bas... i doesn't want to give me some ammo.-More monsters. Where do they come from?-Ok righ... thanks for stealing the ammo I need!-WTF ?! We haven't done the objectives and we have to evac?!-It's crowed out here... I hope I will keep theses meat bags alive without ammo.-What he is doing?! The damm VIP is running into the danger![Dead]-This boss sucks.-Thanks for the help guys![Disconnected]Sorry but for the moment we can't play correctly because there is no way to prepare the attack or talk in game. For a tactical game it's a bit difficult to accept.So actually all games i've played failed, even in easy mode.I tried to do my best as a medic but seriously it doesn't appeal to take the role of support in this game. It seems more efficient to kill everything...And the controls are bad, moving should be with the keyboard.There is a great potential but actually the game is unplayable.And if you don't like this review, well... thank you !Because with your help other players will be completely wrong about this game.And it's not because of Early access. I've changed some of my reviews in front of the state of the game..."
